cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing and text representation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a probabilistic generative model for text representation, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model uses word co-occurrence information and corpus-wide information, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV).
